Fkarnataka-news%2Fhassan-kidnapping-video-teacher-grabbed-pushed-into-suv-in-daylight-karnataka-kidnapping-4620990%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Rural%20Consumption%20Sees%20Slowest%20Growth%20in%20Eight%20Quarters%20During%20July-September%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F02%2F13125046%2Fagriculture-copy.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Rural%20consumption%20experienced%20a%20mere%200.5%25%20year-on-year%20growth%20in%20the%20second%20quarter%20of%20fiscal%20year%202024%2C%20marking%20the%20slowest%20pace%20in%20eight%20quarters%2C%20a%20new%20report%20has%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20contrasts%20with%20urban%20consumption%2C%20which%20grew%207.4%25%20in%20July-September%202023%2C%20the%20highest%20rate%20in%20four%20quarters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20an%20analysis%20by%20Motilal%20Oswal%20Financial%20Services%20(MOFSL)%2C%20the%20tepid%20consumption%20scenario%20in%20rural%20areas%20was%20mainly%20led%20by%20sharply%20deteriorating%20reservoir%20level%2C%20the%20first%20fall%20in%20two-wheeler%20sales%20in%20six%20quarters%2C%20and%20first%20contraction%20in%20fertilizer%20sales%20in%20seven%20quarters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETractor%20sales%20also%20decreased%20for%20the%20second%20consecutive%20quarter%2C%20coupled%20with%20a%20decline%20in%20real%20farm%20exports%20for%20the%20fourth%20straight%20quarter%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.financialexpress.com%2Fpolicy%2Feconomy-rural-consumption-tepid-q2-growth-slowest-in-8-quarters-3321097%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EFinancial%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%2C%20citing%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COur%20analysis%20is%20also%20supported%20by%20the%20MGNREGA%20(Mahatma%20Gandhi%20Rural%20Employment%20Guarantee%20Act)%20data.%20Employment%20demand%20by%20households%20under%20MGNREGA%20was%20much%20higher%20in%20the%20first%20seven%20months%20of%20FY24%20compared%20with%20FY23%20and%20FY18-20%20average%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20agency%20said%2C%20as%20per%20the%20newspaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAround%2022%20million%20people%20demanded%20employment%20under%20MGNREGA%20each%20in%20September%20and%20October%2C%2010-18%25%20higher%20than%20in%20the%20corresponding%20months%20of%20FY23%2C%20and%2026-31%25%20higher%20than%20the%20pre-COVID%20period%2C%20said%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHDFC%20Bank%E2%80%99s%20economist%20Swati%20Arora%20told%20the%20business%20daily%20that%20uneven%20monsoon%20led%20to%20crop%20damage%2C%20which%20weighed%20on%20rural%20consumption.%20She%20added%20that%20higher%20inflation%20added%20to%20the%20woes%20and%20also%20weighed%20on%20discretionary%20spending.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20the%20gap%20between%20rural%20and%20urban%20demand%20is%20likely%20to%20reduce%20in%20Q3%20FY24.%20She%20told%20the%20newspaper%20that%20pre-election%20revenue%20spending%20(such%20as%20LPG%20Price%20cut%2C%20fertiliser%20and%20LPG%20subsidy%2C%20and%20extension%20of%20free%20food%20grain%20programme)%20bodes%20well%20for%20rural%20consumption.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMOFSL%E2%80%99s%20chief%20economist%20Nikhil%20Gupta%20told%20%3Cem%3EFE%20t%3C%2Fem%3Ehat%20%E2%80%9Cwith%20five%20state%20assemblies%20going%20into%20elections%20over%20the%20next%20month%20and%20general%20elections%20scheduled%20in%20May%202024%2C%20the%20hope%20of%20a%20revival%20in%20the%20rural%20sector%20is%20alive.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701336616000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F02%2F13125046%2Fagriculture-copy.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Frural-consumption-sees-slowest-growth-in-eight-quarters-during-july-september-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%20contrasts%20with%20urban%20consumption%2C%20which%20grew%207.4%25%20in%20July-September%202023%2C%20the%20highest%20rate%20in%20four%20quarters.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22